    text: "Aldrich Ames was a high-ranking officer in the CIA. His job was to find Soviet spies, but he had a secret problem: he needed money for his expensive life. In 1985, he decided to sell American secrets to the Soviet Union. For nine years, he gave the Soviets the names of almost every agent working for the US inside Russia. Because of his betrayal, many of these agents were arrested and executed. Ames received millions of dollars for his work as a double agent. He bought a fast car and a big house, which made the FBI very suspicious. After a long investigation, they found proof in his trash and arrested him in 1994. He was sent to prison for the rest of his life. This was one of the most damaging cases in the history of American intelligence because Ames destroyed the entire network of US spies in the Soviet Union.",
