    text: "Ashraf Marwan was a very powerful man in Egypt. He was the son-in-law of the Egyptian President and a close advisor to the government. Because of his position, he knew all of Egypt's military secrets. In 1969, he contacted the Israeli intelligence agency and offered to be a spy. The Israelis gave him the code name 'The Angel.' For several years, he gave Israel very important information about Egypt's plans for war. His most famous moment happened in 1973. He warned Israel that Egypt and Syria were going to attack the very next day. This allowed Israel to prepare for the Yom Kippur War just in time. Marwan died in 2007 when he fell from a balcony in London. Some people believe he was a true spy for Israel, while others think he was a double agent who was actually working for Egypt.",
