    text: "Joe Pistone was an FBI agent who carried out a very dangerous undercover mission. He used the name 'Donnie Brasco' and pretended to be a jewel thief. His goal was to infiltrate the Bonanno crime family in New York. Pistone was so good at his job that the Mafia members trusted him like a brother. He spent six years living a double life. He had to be very careful every day because if the Mafia found out he was a cop, they would kill him. He recorded many conversations and learned about murders and robberies. When the mission ended in 1981, his evidence led to over 200 arrests of top Mafia leaders. The Mafia was so angry that they offered $500,000 to anyone who could kill him. Pistone had to live in hiding for many years. His story is one of the most successful examples of police infiltration in history.",
