    text: "Duško Popov was a wealthy man from Yugoslavia who became a legendary double agent during World War II. He was very charming and loved a luxury life with fast cars and fancy parties. The Nazis recruited him to spy on Britain, but he immediately went to the British and offered to work for them. The British gave him the code name 'Tricycle.' He gave the Nazis fake information that was actually written by British intelligence. He was so trusted by the Germans that they gave him a lot of money and even a special camera to take photos. One of his most important moments was when he tried to warn the Americans about the attack on Pearl Harbor, but they paid him no attention. Popov’s real-life adventures were so exciting and dangerous that he was the main inspiration for the character James Bond.",
