    text: "Eli Cohen was a legendary Israeli spy who was born in Egypt. He was recruited by Mossad to infiltrate the Syrian government. He moved to Damascus and pretended to be a rich Syrian businessman named Kamel Amin Thaabet. He became close friends with top military generals and leaders. Cohen was so successful that he was even invited to visit secret military bunkers. While there, he suggested that the soldiers plant trees for shade. These trees later helped the Israeli army see exactly where the bunkers were. He sent secret messages back to Israel every night using a radio. However, Syrian security caught him in 1965 using special equipment. He was executed in public, but he is remembered as one of Israel's greatest heroes because his information helped them win the Six-Day War.",
