    text: "Mata Hari was a famous exotic dancer from the Netherlands. She traveled all over Europe and became popular with high-ranking military officers and politicians. When World War I started, her ability to travel between countries made her very interesting to intelligence agencies. She was recruited by the French to spy on the Germans, but the Germans also tried to use her. She loved a luxury lifestyle and needed money, which led her into a dangerous double life. In 1917, the French intercepted German radio messages that seemed to prove she was a German agent. The French arrested her and put her on trial for spying. Although the evidence showed no real strength, she was executed by a firing squad near Paris. To this day, people still wonder if she was a real spy or just a victim of the war.",
