    text: "Michael Malone was a quiet and patient undercover agent for the United States government. During the 1920s, the famous mob boss Al Capone controlled Chicago with violence. The police found no way to catch him because he was too powerful. Malone was chosen to infiltrate Capone’s gang. He used a fake name and moved into a hotel where the gang members lived. He spent two years as a member of the group, listening to their conversations and finding out who handled the money. Malone discovered that Capone paid no taxes on the millions of dollars he made from crime. He found the secret bookkeepers and convinced them to talk. Because of Malone's undercover work, the government finally put Al Capone in prison for tax evasion. He is the man who truly destroyed the most famous criminal in history.",
