    text: "Noor Inayat Khan was a princess of Indian descent who lived in France and England. When World War II started, she wanted to help fight the Nazis. She was recruited to be a radio operator in occupied Paris. Her mission was very dangerous because the average life of a radio operator in Paris was only six weeks. Her code name was 'Madeleine.' When her entire spy network was arrested, she refused to leave and stayed to be the only link between London and the French Resistance. She moved from house to house every day with her radio to avoid being caught. Finally, someone betrayed her, and the Nazis arrested her. Even though they tortured her, she gave them no secrets. She was executed in a concentration camp in 1944. She is remembered as a hero of incredible courage.",
