    text: "Oleg Penkovsky was a high-ranking colonel in Soviet military intelligence. He became worried about nuclear war and decided to secretly work for the West. For two years, he provided the CIA with thousands of photos of secret documents about Soviet missiles. His most important contribution happened during the Cuban Missile Crisis in 1962. He gave the Americans the technical manuals for the Soviet missiles being sent to Cuba. This information allowed President Kennedy to know exactly how powerful the missiles were. This knowledge helped Kennedy force the Soviets to remove the missiles and avoid a Third World War. Penkovsky was eventually caught by the KGB and executed in 1963. He is considered a hero for helping to save the world from nuclear destruction.",
