    text: "Ryszard Kukliński was a high-ranking colonel in the Polish army. He had access to all the secret war plans of the Soviet Union. He realized that if a war started, his country would be destroyed. To save Poland, he decided to secretly work for the CIA. For nine years, he took photos of more than 40,000 pages of top-secret Soviet documents. He gave the US the exact plans for a Soviet invasion of Europe. He lived a very stressful double life and was in danger every day. When the Polish security forces began to get close to finding him, the CIA secretly smuggled him and his family out of Poland in a car. He lived in the United States for many years. He is considered a hero because his information helped prevent a Third World War.",
